1 apprenticeship grant program fund shall be for grants awarded pursuant to
2 the Kansas educator registered apprenticeship grant program. All
3 expenditures from the Kansas educator registered apprenticeship grant
4 program fund shall be made in accordance with appropriation acts upon
5 warrants of the director of accounts and reports issued pursuant to
6 vouchers approved by the secretary, or the secretary's designee. All
7 moneys received by the secretary for the Kansas educator registered
8 apprenticeship grant program shall be deposited in the state treasury in
9 accordance with the provisions of K.S.A. 75-4215, and amendments
10 thereto. Upon receipt of each such remittance, the state treasurer shall
11 deposit the entire amount in the state treasury to the credit of the Kansas
12 educator registered apprenticeship grant program fund.
13 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-50,234 is hereby repealed.
14 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
15 publication in the statute book.

